description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Based in Stansted (Essex), this 6 month locum vacancy offers the opportunity for a band 7 or 8a psychologist to join the North West Essex Adult Community Psychology Service. We welcome applications from psychologists who are due to qualify this September/October, as well as from those with more experience. We are also happy to consider those who would like to work part-time and/or flexible hours. Please contact us for an informal discussion if you have any questions about the role.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will join a supportive, highly skilled, established and professional team of psychologists working in Adult Community Mental Health Services in the North-West Essex area of Essex Partnership University Trust. The Psychology service currently comprises approximately seven whole time equivalent Psychologists and three Assistants, together with clinical and counselling psychology trainees and volunteers. We also have close links with colleagues locally working in the 18 – 25’s service, Specialist Dementia &amp; Frailty, Perinatal, Eating Disorders, Urgent Community Care and In Patient settings. Within the service, psychologists have specialist skills and training in variety of areas and approaches, including Autism Spectrum Conditions, CAT, CBT, CBTp, DBT, EMDR, Schema Therapy and Trauma -Informed approaches. Specialist external supervision is provided in several of these approaches, and CPD is both strongly supported and actively encouraged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working alongside other experienced psychologists, the successful applicant will responsible for assessing and formulating with service users presenting with complex needs, and planning, delivering and evaluating interventions. You will promote social inclusion and empower service users within their mental health recovery and in maintaining their social systems. You will also provide consultation and training for staff and others, and placement and supervision for trainee(s) assistant(s) and volunteer(s). This post holder will be working largely with the Uttlesford Specialist Mental Health Service covering Stansted and Saffron Walden. However, some flexibility is needed, and working in other areas may be required as part of the role. The Uttlesford Team has a number of experienced nursing and social work colleagues who have additional training in psychological therapies including CBT and DBT. Although newly formed, the team is cohesive, welcoming and psychologically minded. Team Psychologists work within a non-waiting list model employing a trauma-informed consultation approach to support MDT colleagues to actively engage clients in safety and stabilisation approaches to enable them to make effective use of more formal psychological interventions / therapies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The NW-Essex ACP covers a wide geographical area including Epping Forest, Harlow and Uttlesford. This post will require working with the Uttlesford Locality SMHS based in Stansted, with a satellite base in Saffron Walden. The locality Specialist Adult Community Mental Health Service (MDT) was recently reconfigured to create Neighbourhood based Locality Teams, working with people aged 18+ with Serious Mental Health problems (excluding EIP) in each locality, and with close working relationships with primary care. The Adult Community Psychology Service provides a specialist Psychology service to the service users of these teams, alongside supporting staff and managers. There is a strong focus on evidence based care, and on increasing access to psychological interventions through innovative and efficient evidence-based models of service delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EPUT are looking for motivated staff who shares our Trust values of Open, Compassionate and Empowering. In return, EPUT can offer you a range of benefits and development including;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Season Ticket Loans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS discounts for staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent Training facilities and opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Buying and Selling annual leave scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The opportunity to work bank shifts and expand knowledge and experience in other areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary Sacrifice schemes including lease cars and Cycle to Work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameAstrid PollardJob titleConsultant Clinical PsychologistEmail addressastridpollard@nhs.netTelephone number07866 786 864Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome contact from potential applicants to discuss this vacancy and e.g. possible part-tiem hours or flexible working&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Astrid Pollard, Consultant Clinical Psychologist on 07866 786 864 or Dr Jackie Edwards, Clinical Psychologist on &lt;em&gt;07896 900877 &lt;/em&gt;or jackie.edwards12@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
